=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;"><strong><em>John Heilemann</em></strong><strong>: Having witnessed the =
first week of
Donald Trump=E2=80=99s second term, how are you feeling? </strong><strong><=
br/><br/></strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>Jennifer=
 Palmieri</em>: The thing that I had not predicted was the oligarchs. I fou=
nd it surprisingly upsetting to see them all stand behind Trump=E2=80=94and=
 then, the back-and-forth between <strong>Elon Musk</strong> and <strong>Sa=
m Altman</strong>, being so cavalier and childish with things that are pret=
ty important. In some ways, it=E2=80=99s not as bad to lose this time aroun=
d,
because you=E2=80=99re thinking, <em>Oh yeah, America does stuff like that,=
 </em>like, America elects Trump every now and then. But what is disturbing=
 is the degradation of people who are going down the drain with him. There =
are important things that he did that are troubling, obviously, like the J6=
 pardons, but what concerns me is a degradation of American character, and =
people buying in because they think it=E2=80=99s good for them.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>In his first week in office, the American peopl=
e saw Trump taking a lot of actions, but there=E2=80=99s no focus in Trumpw=
orld. Do you think that=E2=80=99s a problem for them=E2=80=94indiscriminate=
 executive orders as opposed to focusing on the actual things that got him =
reelected?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><br/>If you=
=E2=80=99re working for him, or supported him, you think he had a great fir=
st week because people are so frustrated with government. So if you=E2=80=
=99re paying a
little bit of attention, you=E2=80=99re thinking, <em>All right, he did som=
ething on the border; it seems like he did some executive orders that maybe=
 were meant to try and deal with the economy; he pardoned a bunch of people=
; and the stock market went crazy</em>. So, in the short term, they=E2=80=
=99re happy. But for Democrats, there=E2=80=99s a lot to pick at there: thi=
s A.I. deal that nobody really understands; the lawlessness of letting crim=
inals who have beaten up cops out of jail; the threatening of Panama. I
thought the whole point about all of this was about prices? The stuff that=
=E2=80=99s going to stick, and that people will remember, is the J6 pardons=
=2E<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;ma=
rgin-bottom:0px;"><strong>When you sa=
y you think there=E2=80=99s a price to pay for that, what do you think that=
 price is? Is anybody on the Democratic side doing a good job prosecuting t=
hat case?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p=
 style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">They wanted to not pardon everyone,
but it got complicated, and he was like, <em>Fuck it, just let them all go<=
/em>. That=E2=80=99s playing into an overall vulnerability of his=E2=80=94b=
eing cavalier and not caring about anything but himself. So what I would sa=
y is, he let all these criminals out of jail because it=E2=80=99s always, a=
lways, always about him. He=E2=80=99s still mad about January 6th, and he d=
id this as retribution. It won=E2=80=99t go away, because pardon [recipient=
s] like <strong>Enrique Tarrio</strong> are not being quiet and are saying =
a bunch of
crazy stuff out there.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>There are Democrats w=
ho are effective about it. I think <strong>Jamie</strong> <strong>Raskin</s=
trong> is effective; I think <strong>Hakeem Jeffries</strong> is effective;=
 I think Senator <strong>Adam</strong> <strong>Schiff</strong> is effective=
=2E But it has to take hold over a long=
 period of time. Even the F.O.P. [Frat=
ernal Order of Police] had to come out and chastise him. They=E2=80=99re li=
ke, <em>Whoa, we didn=E2=80=99t think </em>that <em>was gonna
happen.</em></p></div>
