 the House with
A.O.C. and Marjorie Taylor Greene, two of the most polarizing, and compelli=
ng, members of Congress. What do you think about their messages, their move=
ments, and their futures in their respective parties?</strong></p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bott=
om:0px;">They=E2=80=99re both very effective communicators; <strong>A.O.C.<=
/strong> is better than <strong>Marjorie Taylor Greene</strong>. I=E2=80=99=
ve spent a decent amount of time with Marjorie Taylor Greene, certainly
more than most people who aren=E2=80=99t Republicans. She=E2=80=99s smart; =
she knows what she=E2=80=99s doing; she=E2=80=99s very astute about power. =
She knows how to go for the jugular, both in terms of where an opponent is =
weak, and also what people care about. Then, at some point, she takes this =
wild turn that makes you go, <em>Whoa, she is not in touch with reality</em=
>.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"=
margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">It=E2=80=99s hard for me to predict where the =
Republican Party is
going to go, but Ocasio-Cortez really understands power, she does her homew=
ork, and she=E2=80=99s learned how to be effective in Congress. She=E2=80=
=99s going to be around for a long time.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bot=
tom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Who=E2=
=80=99s saying things that matter, and has some kind of a grip on what Demo=
crats need to be doing?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Within D.C., I think H=
akeem
Jeffries and the House Democrats are very disciplined and good at this. The=
re are people who have a specific message, and then there are people who=E2=
=80=99ve just sort of emerged authentically. <strong>Tim Kaine</strong> com=
es to mind; he=E2=80=99s been great. <strong>Tammy Duckworth</strong> was g=
reat at the <strong>Hegseth</strong> hearing. <strong>Elissa</strong> <stro=
ng>Slotkin</strong> was excellent. They=E2=80=99re not pussyfooting around.=
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0=
;
margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>I=E2=80=99m not going to ask you to handicap it=
, but who are the people you think are definitely going to be running in 20=
28?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>It=E2=80=99s going to be unbeli=
evable. There=E2=80=99s a lot of talent: <strong>Gretchen Whitmer</strong>,=
 <strong>Gavin Newsom</strong>, <strong>J.B. Pritzker</strong>, <strong>Pet=
e Buttigieg</strong>, <strong>Chris Murphy</strong>, <strong>Josh Shapiro</=
strong>. Does <strong>John Fetterman</strong> run? Governor <strong>Andy
Beshear</strong> of Kentucky. <strong>Wes Moore</strong>, my governor. <str=
ong>Kamala Harris</strong>!</p></div>
