px;">It doesn=E2=80=99t surprise me, just because I know what happens to wo=
men in the public eye, particularly if they=E2=80=99re not aggressive about=
 being out there and telling their story. I=E2=80=99m interested to know mo=
re about her. This $40 million deal=E2=80=94at a time when the industry is =
going
through hell, and no one has money for political projects=E2=80=94is mind-b=
lowing. It=E2=80=99s mind-blowing that <strong>Bezos</strong> is like, <em>=
Yeah, I=E2=80=99m going to pay $40 million</em>. Melania is getting paid tw=
ice as much as <strong>Billie Eilish </strong>for a documentary that I don=
=E2=80=99t think a lot of people are going to watch.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;"><strong>I want to discuss the Brett Ratner of it all. Trump is interwov=
en in the
#MeToo movement. How do you tell </strong><strong><em>that</em></strong><st=
rong> story, of how Trump has brought us all along the narrative arc of #Me=
Too and all it represents?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0=
px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I think about it we=
ll beyond #MeToo. The rise of women leaders is coinciding with the greatest=
 erosion of women=E2=80=99s rights. I think America would, and will, elect =
a female president. I don=E2=80=99t believe Kamala Harris lost because
she=E2=80=99s a woman. It was <em>harder</em> for her because she was a wom=
an, but there <em>was</em> a man in the race=E2=80=94Joe Biden was in the r=
ace, and Kamala Harris did a lot better than him. Hillary got more votes th=
an Trump. I really don=E2=80=99t feel like men are trying to hold women bac=
k. It=E2=80=99s certainly not my personal experience. But there=E2=80=99s a=
 lot of cultural change happening, and gender and diversity are a part of t=
hat. It=E2=80=99s caused quite a reckoning. You see tech leaders like <stro=
ng>Mark
Zuckerberg</strong>, who, when Trump was in office the first time, said a l=
ot of great stuff about women and diversity; and now that it=E2=80=99s =E2=
=80=9Csafe=E2=80=9D to be super pro-male, he talks about how we need more m=
asculine energy in the C-suite.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">It may take a long time, but I beli=
eve in that long arc. And there will be backlash. Trump was a backlash; and=
 #MeToo and the #Resistance were the backlash to the backlash. And Trump
winning again is a part of the backlash, and there will be another backlash=
=2E But we won=E2=80=99t stay here. Thr=
ee years from now, we=E2=80=99re not g=
oing to be talking about how we don=E2=80=99t listen to masculine energy en=
ough.</p></div>
